The paper discusses a novel framework for evaluating recommendation algorithms based on graph analysis. This approach emphasizes reachability via an algorithm within the implicit graph structure underlying a recommender dataset. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), which deals with the retrieval of information from large datasets. Other likely sub-categories include cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
